 of your conditional statements and how they interact with each other.\n\nCONCEPTS TO REVIEW:\n- Conditional statements (if, else) and their flow of execution.\n\nGUIDING QUESTIONS:\n- What happens when multiple conditions are checked in sequence? \n- How does the placement of the `else` statement affect the output of your code?\n- Can you think of a way to combine the two `if` statements to achieve the desired behavior?\n\nFINAL SCORE:\n5/10  \nReason: The logical flow of the conditions is unclear, leading to potential misunderstandings in the output.\n\nENCOURAGEMENT:\nKeep experimenting with your code, and you\'ll continue to improve your problem-solving skills!','2026-03-07 15:36:00','INCORRECT',90,1,0,70),(40,4,'N/A','from fastapi import FastAPI, Response, status, Query\r\nfrom pydantic import BaseModel\r\n\r\napp = FastAPI()\r\nproducts = [\r\n    {\"id\": 1, \"name\": \"Wireless Mouse\", \"price\": 499, \"category\": \"Electronics\", \"in_stock\": True},\r\n    {\"id\": 2, \"name\": \"Notebook\", \"price\": 99, \"category\": \"Stationery\", \"in_stock\": True},\r\n    {\"id\": 3, \"name\": \"USB Hub\", \"price\": 799, \"category\": \"Electronics\", \"in_stock\": False},\r\n    {\"id\": 4, \"name\": \"Pen Set\", \"price\": 49, \"category\": \"Stationery\", \"in_stock\": True}\r\n]\r\n\r\n\r\nclass NewProduct(BaseModel):\r\n    name: str\r\n    price: int\r\n    category: str\r\n    in_stock: bool = True\r\n\r\n\r\ndef find_product(product_id: int):\r\n    for p in products:\r\n        if p[\"id\"] == product_id:\r\n            return p\r\n    return None\r\n\r\n\r\n@app.get(\"/\")\r\ndef home():\r\n    return {\"message\": \"Product API running\"}\r\n\r\n\r\n@app.get(\"/products\")\r\ndef get_products():\r\n    return {\r\n        \"products\": products,\r\n        \"total\": len(products)\r\n    }\r\n\r\n\r\n@app.get(\"/products/audit\")\r\ndef product_audit():\r\n\r\n    in_stock_list = [p for p in products if p[\"in_stock\"]]\r\n    out_stock_list = [p for p in products if not p[\"in_stock\"]]\r\n\r\n    stock_value = sum(p[\"price\"] * 10 for p in in_stock_list)\r\n\r\n    priciest = max(products, key=lambda p: p[\"price\"])\r\n\r\n    return {\r\n        \"total_products\": len(products),\r\n        \"in_stock_count\": len(in_stock_list),\r\n        \"out_of_stock_names\": [p[\"name\"] for p in out_stock_list],\r\n        \"total_stock_value\": stock_value,\r\n        \"most_expensive\": {\r\n            \"name\": priciest[\"name\"],\r\n            \"price\": priciest[\"price\"]\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n\r\n\r\n@app.put(\"/products/discount\")\r\ndef bulk_discount(\r\n        category: str = Query(...),\r\n        discount_percent: int = Query(..., ge=1, le=99)\r\n):\r\n\r\n    updated = []\r\n\r\n    for p in products:\r\n        if p[\"category\"] == category:\r\n            p[\"price\"] = int(p[\"price\"] * (1 - discount_percent / 100))\r\n            updated.append(p)\r\n\r\n    if not updated:\r\n        return {\"message\": f\"No products found in category: {category}\"}\r\n\r\n    return {\r\n        \"message\": f\"{discount_percent}% discount applied to {category}\",\r\n        \"updated_count\": len(updated),\r\n        \"updated_products\": updated\r\n    }\r\n\r\n\r\n@app.get(\"/products/{product_id}\")\r\ndef get_product(product_id: int, response: Response):\r\n\r\n    product = find_product(product_id)\r\n\r\n    if not product:\r\n        response.status_code = status.HTTP_404_NOT_FOUND\r\n        return {\"error\": \"Product not found\"}\r\n\r\n    return product\r\n\r\n\r\n@app.post(\"/products\", status_code=201)\r\ndef add_product(product: NewProduct, response: Response):\r\n\r\n    for p in products:\r\n        if p[\"name\"].lower() == product.name.lower():\r\n            response.status_code = status.HTTP_400_BAD_REQUEST\r\n            return {\"error\": \"Product with this name already exists\"}\r\n\r\n    next_id = max(p[\"id\"] for p in products) + 1\r\n\r\n    new_product = {\r\n        \"id\": next_id,\r\n        \"name\": product.name,\r\n        \"price\": product.price,\r\n        \"category\": product.category,\r\n        \"in_stock\": product.in_stock\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    products.append(new_product)\r\n\r\n    return {\r\n        \"message\": \"Product added\",\r\n        \"product\": new_product\r\n    }\r\n\r\n\r\n@app.put(\"/products/{product_id}\")\r\ndef update_product(\r\n        product_id: int,\r\n        response: Response,\r\n        price: int = None,\r\n        in_stock: bool = None\r\n):\r\n\r\n    product = find_product(product_id)\r\n\r\n    if not product:\r\n        response.status_code = status.HTTP_404_NOT_FOUND\r\n        return {\"error\": \"Product not found\"}\r\n\r\n    if price is not None:\r\n        product[\"price\"] = price\r\n\r\n    if in_stock is not None:\r\n        product[\"in_stock\"] = in_stock\r\n\r\n    return {\r\n        \"message\": \"Product updated\",\r\n        \"product\": product\r\n    }\r\n\r\n\r\n@app.delete(\"/products/{product_id}\")\r\ndef delete_product(product_id: int, response: Response):\r\n\r\n    product = find_product(product_id)\r\n\r\n    if not product:\r\n        response.status_code = status.HTTP_404_NOT_FOUND\r\n        return {\"error\": \"Product not found\"}\r\n\r\n    products.remove(product)\r\n\r\n    return {\"message\": f\"Product \'{product[\'name\']}\' deleted\"}','**THINGS DONE WELL:**\n- The code is well-structured and follows RESTful API principles effectively.\n- Clear separation of concerns, with distinct functions for each endpoint.\n- Good use of Pydantic for data validation with the `NewProduct` model.\n- Comprehensive handling of product-related operations, including creation, retrieval, updating, and deletion.\n- Effective use of list comprehensions for filtering products and calculating stock values.\n\n**LOGICAL ANALYSIS:**\n- The code works because it utilizes FastAPI\'s routing capabilities to define endpoints that correspond to CRUD operations on a product inventory. Each function handles specific requests and responses, ensuring that the API behaves predictably. The use of helper functions (like `find_product`) and data models (via Pydantic) enhances maintainability and clarity.\n\n**FINAL SCORE:**\n9/10  \nReason: The implementation is robust and covers a wide range of functionalities, but could benefit from additional error handling for edge cases.\n\n**ENCOURAGEMENT:**\n- Great job on creating a functional and organized API—keep up the excellent work!','2026-03-13 01:37:00','CORRECT',95,0,1,85),(41,4,'N/A','from flask import Flask, render_template, request, jsonify, session, redirect\r\nimport json\r\nfrom datetime import datetime\r\nfrom openai import OpenAI\r\nimport config\r\nimport re\r\nfrom flask_mysqldb import MySQL\r\n\r\napp = Flask(__name__)\r\napp.config[\'SECRET_KEY\'] = config.secret_key\r\n\r\nclient = OpenAI(api_key=config.api_key)\r\n# MySQL Configuration\r\napp.config[\'MYSQL_HOST\'] = \'localhost\'\r\napp.config[\'MYSQL_USER\'] = \'root\'\r\napp.config[\'MYSQL_PASSWORD\'] = \'6827\'\r\napp.config[\'MYSQL_DB\'] = \'ai_code_mentor\'\r\n\r\nmysql = MySQL(app)\r\n# Logging System\r\ndef log_event(data):\r\n    data[\"timestamp\"] = str(datetime.now())\r\n    with open(\"system_logs.json\", \"a\") as f:\r\n        f.write(json.dumps(data) + \"\\n\")\r\n\r\n# -------------------------\r\n# Code Validation\r\n# -------------------------\r\ndef validate_code(code):\r\n    if not code.strip():\r\n        return False, \"Code is empty.\"\r\n\r\n    try:\r\n        compile(code, \"<string>\", \"exec\")\r\n    except Exception as e:\r\n        return False, f\"Syntax Error: {str(e)}\"\r\n\r\n    return True, \"Valid\"\r\n\r\n# -------------------------\r\n# STRICT VERDICT CHECK\r\n# -------------------------\r\ndef get_verdict(code):\r\n\r\n    prompt = f\"\"\"\r\nYou are a strict logical evaluator.\r\n\r\nAnalyze this Python code:\r\n\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nRespond EXACTLY in this format:\r\n\r\nVERDICT: CORRECT or INCORRECT\r\nCONFIDENCE: X%\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\n    response = client.chat.completions.create(\r\n        model=config.model_name,\r\n        temperature=0,\r\n        messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": prompt}]\r\n    )\r\n\r\n    text = response.choices[0].message.content\r\n\r\n    verdict_match = re.search(r\"VERDICT:\\s*(CORRECT|INCORRECT)\", text)\r\n    confidence_match = re.search(r\"CONFIDENCE:\\s*(\\d+)%\", text)\r\n\r\n    verdict = verdict_match.group(1) if verdict_match else \"INCORRECT\"\r\n    confidence = int(confidence_match.group(1)) if confidence_match else 50\r\n\r\n    return verdict, confidence\r\n\r\n# -------------------------\r\n# TIME COMPLEXITY\r\n# -------------------------\r\ndef get_time_complexity(code):\r\n\r\n    prompt = f\"\"\"\r\nAnalyze the following Python code:\r\n\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nProvide ONLY:\r\n\r\nTIME COMPLEXITY:\r\nO(...)\r\nShort explanation.\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\n    response = client.chat.completions.create(\r\n        model=config.model_name,\r\n        temperature=0,\r\n        messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": prompt}]\r\n    )\r\n\r\n    return response.choices[0].message.content.strip()\r\n\r\n# -------------------------\r\n# SPACE COMPLEXITY\r\n# -------------------------\r\ndef get_space_complexity(code):\r\n\r\n    prompt = f\"\"\"\r\nAnalyze the following Python code:\r\n\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nProvide ONLY:\r\n\r\nSPACE COMPLEXITY:\r\nO(...)\r\nShort explanation.\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\n    response = client.chat.completions.create(\r\n        model=config.model_name,\r\n        temperature=0,\r\n        messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": prompt}]\r\n    )\r\n\r\n    return response.choices[0].message.content.strip()\r\n\r\n# -------------------------\r\n# SMART MENTOR FEEDBACK\r\n# -------------------------\r\ndef get_feedback(code, verdict):\r\n\r\n    if verdict == \"CORRECT\":\r\n\r\n        prompt = f\"\"\"\r\nYou are a supportive coding mentor.\r\n\r\nThis code is logically correct:\r\n\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nProvide ONLY:\r\n\r\nTHINGS DONE WELL:\r\n- Clear strengths.\r\n\r\nLOGICAL ANALYSIS:\r\n- Why it works.\r\n\r\nFINAL SCORE:\r\nX/10\r\nReason: short justification.\r\n\r\nENCOURAGEMENT:\r\n- One motivating sentence.\r\n\r\nDo NOT suggest improvements.\r\nDo NOT invent problems.\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\n    else:\r\n\r\n        prompt = f\"\"\"\r\nYou are a supportive coding mentor.\r\n\r\nThis code has logical issues:\r\n\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nProvide ONLY:\r\n\r\nTHINGS TO RETHINK:\r\n- Weak areas.\r\n\r\nCONCEPTS TO REVIEW:\r\n- Relevant topics.\r\n\r\nGUIDING QUESTIONS:\r\n- Ask thinking-based questions.\r\n- Do NOT give full solution.\r\n\r\nFINAL SCORE:\r\nX/10\r\nReason: short justification.\r\n\r\nENCOURAGEMENT:\r\n- One motivating sentence.\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\n    response = client.chat.completions.create(\r\n        model=config.model_name,\r\n        temperature=config.temperature_review,\r\n        messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": prompt}]\r\n    )\r\n\r\n    return response.choices[0].message.content.strip()\r\n\r\n# -------------------------\r\n# AI / PLAGIARISM DETECTION\r\n# -------------------------\r\ndef detect_ai_generated(code):\r\n\r\n    prompt = f\"\"\"\r\nYou are an expert in detecting AI-generated programming code.\r\n\r\nAnalyze this Python code:\r\n\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nRespond EXACTLY in this format:\r\n\r\nAI_PROBABILITY: X%\r\nVERDICT: AI or HUMAN\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\n    response = client.chat.completions.create(\r\n        model=config.model_name,\r\n        temperature=0,\r\n        messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": prompt}]\r\n    )\r\n\r\n    text = response.choices[0].message.content\r\n\r\n    match = re.search(r\'AI_PROBABILITY:\\s*(\\d+)%\', text)\r\n    probability = int(match.group(1)) if match else 0\r\n\r\n    verdict = \"AI\" if probability >= 75 else \"HUMAN\"\r\n\r\n    return probability, verdict\r\n\r\n# -------------------------\r\n# Home\r\n# -------------------------\r\n@app.route(\"/\")\r\ndef home():\r\n    if \"user_id\" not in session:\r\n        return redirect(\"/login\")\r\n    return render_template(\"index.html\")\r\n\r\n# -------------------------\r\n# Review Route\r\n# -------------------------\r\n@app.route(\"/review\", methods=[\"POST\"])\r\ndef review():\r\n\r\n    if \"user_id\" not in session:\r\n        return jsonify({\"review\": \"Please login first.\"})\r\n\r\n    code = request.form[\"code\"]\r\n\r\n    valid, message = validate_code(code)\r\n    if not valid:\r\n        return jsonify({\"review\": message})\r\n\r\n    try:\r\n        verdict, confidence = get_verdict(code)\r\n\r\n        feedback = get_feedback(code, verdict)\r\n\r\n        time_complexity = get_time_complexity(code) if verdict == \"CORRECT\" else None\r\n        space_complexity = get_space_complexity(code) if verdict == \"CORRECT\" else None\r\n\r\n        ai_probability, ai_verdict = detect_ai_generated(code)\r\n        ai_flag = ai_probability >= 75\r\n\r\n        # Store in DB\r\n        cur = mysql.connection.cursor()\r\n        error_count = 0 if verdict == \"CORRECT\" else 1\r\n\r\n        cur.execute(\"\"\"\r\nINSERT INTO submissions\r\n(user_id, goal, code, feedback, verdict, confidence, error_count, plagiarism_flag, plagiarism_probability)\r\nVALUES (%s,%s,%s,%s,%s,%s,%s,%s,%s)\r\n\"\"\",\r\n(\r\n    session[\"user_id\"],\r\n    \"N/A\",\r\n    code,\r\n    feedback,\r\n    verdict,\r\n    confidence,\r\n    error_count,\r\n    ai_flag,\r\n    ai_probability\r\n))\r\n        mysql.connection.commit()\r\n        cur.close()\r\n\r\n        log_event({\r\n            \"type\": \"review\",\r\n            \"correctness\": verdict,\r\n            \"confidence\": confidence,\r\n            \"ai_probability\": ai_probability\r\n        })\r\n\r\n        return jsonify({\r\n            \"feedback\": feedback,\r\n            \"verdict\": verdict,\r\n            \"confidence\": confidence,\r\n            \"time_complexity\": time_complexity,\r\n            \"space_complexity\": space_complexity,\r\n            \"plagiarism_flag\": ai_flag,\r\n            \"plagiarism_probability\": ai_probability if ai_flag else None\r\n        })\r\n\r\n    except Exception as e:\r\n        log_event({\"type\": \"error\", \"error\": str(e)})\r\n        return jsonify({\"review\": \"AI evaluation failed.\"})\r\n@app.route(\"/login\", methods=[\"GET\", \"POST\"])\r\ndef login():\r\n    if request.method == \"POST\":\r\n        email = request.form[\"email\"]\r\n        password = request.form[\"password\"]\r\n\r\n        cur = mysql.connection.cursor()\r\n        cur.execute(\r\n            \"SELECT * FROM users WHERE email=%s AND password=%s\",\r\n            (email, password)\r\n        )\r\n        user = cur.fetchone()\r\n        cur.close()\r\n\r\n        if user:\r\n            session[\"user_id\"] = user[0]\r\n            return redirect(\"/\")\r\n        else:\r\n            return \"Invalid credentials\"\r\n\r\n    return render_template(\"login.html\")\r\n@app.route(\"/signup\", methods=[\"GET\", \"POST\"])\r\ndef signup():\r\n    if request.method == \"POST\":\r\n        name = request.form[\"name\"]\r\n        email = request.form[\"email\"]\r\n        password = request.form[\"password\"]\r\n\r\n        cur = mysql.connection.cursor()\r\n        cur.execute(\r\n            \"INSERT INTO users(name,email,password) VALUES(%s,%s,%s)\",\r\n            (name, email, password)\r\n        )\r\n        mysql.connection.commit()\r\n        cur.close()\r\n\r\n        return redirect(\"/login\")\r\n\r\n    return render_template(\"signup.html\")\r\n@app.route(\"/profile\")\r\ndef profile():\r\n\r\n    if \"user_id\" not in session:\r\n        return redirect(\"/login\")\r\n\r\n    user_id = session[\"user_id\"]\r\n\r\n    cur = mysql.connection.cursor()\r\n\r\n    # Get user name\r\n    cur.execute(\"SELECT name FROM users WHERE id=%s\", (user_id,))\r\n    user = cur.fetchone()\r\n\r\n    # Get statistics\r\n    cur.execute(\"\"\"\r\n    SELECT \r\n    COUNT(*) AS total_submissions,\r\n    SUM(error_count) AS total_errors,\r\n    SUM(plagiarism_flag) AS plagiarism_count\r\n    FROM submissions\r\n    WHERE user_id=%s\r\n    \"\"\", (user_id,))\r\n    \r\n    stats = cur.fetchone()\r\n\r\n    # Submission history\r\n    cur.execute(\"\"\"\r\n    SELECT verdict, confidence, plagiarism_flag, plagiarism_probability\r\n    FROM submissions\r\n    WHERE user_id=%s\r\n    ORDER BY id DESC\r\n    LIMIT 10\r\n    \"\"\", (user_id,))\r\n    \r\n    history = cur.fetchall()\r\n\r\n    # Leaderboard\r\n    cur.execute(\"\"\"\r\n    SELECT \r\n    u.name,\r\n    SUM(s.error_count) AS errors,\r\n    SUM(s.plagiarism_flag) AS plagiarism\r\n    FROM users u\r\n    JOIN submissions s ON u.id = s.user_id\r\n    GROUP BY u.id\r\n    ORDER BY plagiarism ASC, errors ASC\r\n    LIMIT 5\r\n    \"\"\")\r\n\r\n    leaderboard = cur.fetchall()\r\n\r\n    cur.close()\r\n\r\n    return render_template(\r\n        \"profile.html\",\r\n        name=user[0],\r\n        submissions=stats[0] or 0,\r\n        errors=stats[1] or 0,\r\n        plagiarism=stats[2] or 0,\r\n        history=history,\r\n        leaderboard=leaderboard\r\n    )\r\n@app.route(\"/logout\")\r\ndef logout():\r\n    session.clear()\r\n    return redirect(\"/login\")\r\n# -------------------------\r\n# Run\r\n# -------------------------\r\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\r\n    app.run(debug=True)','THINGS DONE WELL:\n- The code is well-structured and modular, making it easy to read and maintain.\n- It effectively uses Flask for web routing and session management.\n- The integration with OpenAI\'s API for code analysis and feedback is well-executed.\n- Database interactions with MySQL are handled properly, ensuring data persistence.\n- Comprehensive logging of events and errors helps in monitoring and debugging.\n\nLOGICAL ANALYSIS:\n- The application logically validates user input, ensuring that only valid code is processed.\n- It utilizes AI to evaluate code correctness, provide feedback, and detect AI-generated content, enhancing the user experience.\n- The use of session management ensures that only authenticated users can access certain functionalities, maintaining security.\n\nFINAL SCORE:\n9/10\nReason: The application demonstrates strong functionality, effective use of libraries, and good coding practices. It could benefit from additional error handling and security measures, but overall, it performs excellently.\n\nENCOURAGEMENT:\n- Keep up the great work! Your coding skills are clearly developing, and this project showcases your ability to integrate various technologies effectively.','2026-03-13 01:38:53','CORRECT',85,0,1,85),(42,4,'N/A','def min_coins(amount):\r\n    denominations = [2000, 500, 200, 100, 50, 20, 10, 5, 2, 1]\r\n    count = 0\r\n\r\n    for coin in denominations:\r\n        if amount >= coin:\r\n            num = amount // coin\r\n            count += num\r\n            amount -= num * coin\r\n            print(coin, \":\", num)\r\n\r\n    print(\"Total coins/notes:\", count)\r\n\r\nmin_coins(2758)','THINGS DONE WELL:\n- The code is well-structured and easy to read, with clear variable names and a logical flow.\n- The use of a list to store denominations allows for easy adjustments and scalability.\n- The print statements effectively provide feedback on the number of each denomination used.\n\nLOGICAL ANALYSIS:\n- The function iterates through the list of denominations, checking if the current denomination can be used to make up the given amount. It calculates how many coins/notes of that denomination are needed, updates the total count, and reduces the remaining amount accordingly. This greedy algorithm ensures that the minimum number of coins/notes is used.\n\nFINAL SCORE:\n9/10  \nReason: The code is efficient and logically sound, but could benefit from additional comments for clarity.\n\nENCOURAGEMENT:\n- Great job on creating a clear and efficient solution; keep up the fantastic work!','2026-03-13 05:33:14','C