 sound, ensuring that nodes are linked correctly.\n\nFINAL SCORE:\n9/10  \nReason: The implementation is solid, but adding error handling for edge cases (like inserting into an empty list) could enhance robustness.\n\nENCOURAGEMENT:\n- Great job on this implementation! Keep up the fantastic work and continue to explore more complex data structures!','2026-03-14 04:58:36','CORRECT',95,0,0,70),(61,4,'N/A','# Node class\r\nclass Node:\r\n    def __init__(self, data):\r\n        self.data = data\r\n        self.next = None\r\n\r\n\r\n# Linked List class\r\nclass LinkedList:\r\n    def __init__(self):\r\n        self.head = None\r\n\r\n    # Insert at beginning\r\n    def insert_beginning(self, data):\r\n        new_node = Node(data)\r\n        new_node.next = self.head\r\n        self.head = new_node\r\n\r\n    # Insert at end\r\n    def insert_end(self, data):\r\n        new_node = Node(data)\r\n\r\n        if self.head is None:\r\n            self.head = new_node\r\n            return\r\n\r\n        temp = self.head\r\n        while temp.next:\r\n            temp = temp.next\r\n\r\n        temp.next = new_node\r\n\r\n    # Display linked list\r\n    def display(self):\r\n        temp = self.head\r\n        while temp:\r\n            print(temp.data, end=\" -> \")\r\n            temp = temp.next\r\n        print(\"None\")\r\n\r\n\r\n# Creating linked list\r\nll = LinkedList()\r\n\r\nll.insert_beginning(10)\r\nll.insert_beginning(5)\r\nll.insert_end(20)\r\nll.insert_end(30)\r\n\r\nprint(\"Linked List:\")\r\nll.display()','THINGS DONE WELL:\n- The code is well-structured with clear class definitions for `Node` and `LinkedList`.\n- The methods for inserting nodes at the beginning and end are implemented correctly.\n- The display method effectively shows the linked list in a readable format.\n\nLOGICAL ANALYSIS:\n- The `Node` class encapsulates the data and the reference to the next node, allowing for dynamic linking. The `LinkedList` class manages the head of the list and